Senegal elects president Senegalese vote in a presidential election in which the incumbent Macky Sally is highly tipped to win. Nigeria counts vote Nigerians await the result of a presidential election after casting their ballots in a poll considered a two-horse race between the incumbent President Muhammadu Buhari and former Vice-President Atiku Abubakar. No let-up in Sudan Besieged Sudanese President Omar al-Bashir declares a national state of emergency, dismisses the federal government and sacks all state governors. Anger in Algeria Algerians to hold demonstrations against a fifth mandate for the ailing President Abdulaziz Bouteflika. Egypt hosts summit The European Union and Arab League summit takes place in the Egyptian resort city of Sharm El-Sheikh. Prince visits MoroccoBritain's Prince Harry and Meghan visit till Wednesday Burkina film festival The Pan-African film and television festival takes place in Burkina Faso capital Ouagadougou. Confederation Cup clash Kenya's soccer champions Gor Mahia take on Algeria's Nas Athletique de Husein Dey in the Caf Confederation Group D clash at the Moi International Sports Centre, Kasarani in Nairobi.   Pontiff compares paedophilia to human sacrifice Kenyans claw their way back on top of the group table